UTF8Strings
------------------------------------------
UTF8 Strings as a C++ library that provides ability to work natively with UTF8
strings in a very simple way.

All you get is UTF8::String class with many overloaded operators and serving
functions. You can concatenate strings just with + operator, assign one to
another, convert to and from integer, get substring, replace and so on. And
all the time content of the string is native UTF8 sequence which you can
access too.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.9.0-3
  libgcc1-6.4.0-4
  libstdc++6-6.4.0-4
  libUTF8Strings1-1.14.2-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.25.0-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-4
  gcc-g++-6.4.0-4
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://grigory.info/UTF8Strings.About.html

Canonical download:
  http://grigory.info/distfiles/UTF8Strings-1.14.2.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack UTF8Strings-1.14.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./UTF8Strings-1.14.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/UTF8Strings-1.14.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/UTF8Strings-1.14.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libUTF8Strings1-1.14.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libUTF8Strings-devel-1.14.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(UTF8Strings)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/UTF8Strings.README
  /usr/share/doc/UTF8Strings/ChangeLog.txt

(libUTF8Strings1)
  /usr/bin/cygUTF8Strings-1.dll

(libUTF8Strings-devel)
  /usr/include/UTF8Strings-1/Exception.h
  /usr/include/UTF8Strings-1/String.h
  /usr/lib/libUTF8Strings-1.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/UTF8Strings.pc

